Biker reacts lightning fast and prevents worse
On Friday evening, a traffic accident occurred on the highway between Machtolsheim and Merklingen, in which a motorcyclist was only slightly injured thanks to his rapid reaction.
Driver overlooks biker
A 44-year-old driver wanted to turn left on the Landesstraße 1230 towards Machtolsheim at around 9.30 p.m. with her VW from Merklingen.
She overlooked the 24-year-old motorad driver coming from the direction of Nellingen.
In the collision, hand and foot brake levers fly away
The biker tried to evade the passenger car, but still roamed it at the rear of the vehicle.
Due to the patrol, the hand and foot brake levers were torn off at the Suzuki and the driver was no longer able to brake.
At the moment of his mind, he steered his motorcycle in the green bar next to the road and had it rolled out there without falling.
Biker suffers leg injury
Due to the collision with the car, the biker still suffered an injury on the side and had to be treated in a clinic.
Mamming: Corona mass infection: 174 harvest helpers infected
After a Corona mass infection on a large vegetable farm in Mamming in Lower Bavaria, nearly 500 people are quarantined and are no longer allowed to leave the farm.
A security department is monitoring the ban on going out.
A total of 174 harvest helpers were tested positive for the Corona pathogen Sars-CoV-2 during the series investigation, as the Dingolfing-Landau Landratsamt reported on Saturday evening.
"Unfortunately, in order to avoid further spread, we have to take this step to protect the population," explained Landrat Werner Bumeder (CSU).
Previously, seven employees had already infected themselves in the company - this was the reason for the series test.
The farm is a large vegetable farm that cultivates strawberries, cucumbers, cabbage and beetroot - but the cucumbers only for inlaid glasses.
Mamming is a rural community with about 3300 inhabitants near Dingolfing with its large BMW plant.
Bumeder appealed to the citizens to keep quiet: "According to our information, this is a closed circle of people".
At the farm, infected people were separated from non-infected employees, the grounds are now surrounded by a barrier fence.
Greens and SPD gave the state government co-responsibility.
The two opposition factions accused Prime Minister Markus Söder (CSU) and his cabinet of neglecting the control of the accommodations of seasonal workers.
"This can be bitterly avengeable if such local infection occurs and regional lockdowns have to be ordered," said Jürgen Mistol, the parliamentary managing director of the Greens.
This is quite similar to the SPD: "After the Corona outbreak in the Wiesenhof-Schlachthhof in mid-May, we have already called for a special control programme for farms with harvest helpers," said environmental expert Florian von Brunn.
"Especially the hygiene conditions at the workplace and the housing conditions must be strictly controlled from our point of view.
This obviously did not happen."
The outbreak had come "with announcement".
