In a dispute between two youth groups at the Aidenbachstraße underground station, a 19-year-old fell through a pusher and slipped into the track bed.
Obersendling - On Friday there was a dispute between two youth groups at the Aidenbachstraße underground station around 4.15 p.m.
A passerby alerted the police, who moved in with several stripes.
According to the first investigation, a Munich (17) pushed a 19-year-old down.
The young man slipped over the edge of the platform and fell into the track bed.
People from the group of the 17-year-old helped to climb the fallen out of the track.
There was no danger from a boarding train.
According to the police, there were conflicts between the two people again.
The 17-year-old fled from the crime scene, but his personalities could be investigated afterwards.
Accompanied by his father, he went to police inspection 29.
