Freital: Windbergfest cancelled because of Corona
The Windbergfest does not take place this year.
The city of Freital has cancelled the three-day festival planned in September.
In other years, over 30,000 people had attended this city festival.
"We really didn't make this decision easy and - knowing how difficult it is economically for the parties involved - hoped until the last minute," said Mayor Uwe Rumberg (non-partisan).
"But in the end, we are responsible here as organisers for the health of many thousands of people."
Because if tens of thousands had flowed to the festival grounds and into the marquee, minimum distances, hygiene regulations as well as a follow-up to the current Corona protection regulation could not have been complied with.
Or the restrictions would have been so strong that there wouldn't have been much left of a folk festival.
Moreover, the organisational and monitoring burden would rise disproportionately by many times.
Rumberg comforted next year.
Then the city of Freital celebrates its 100th anniversary with the Winterbergfest from 7 to 9 May 2021 and the day of Saxony from 10 to 12 September 2021.
