More air traffic controllers in Worms in the future
The University of Worms goes further into the air: The "DFS Deutsche Flugsicherung" (DFS Deutsche Flugsicherung) provides a professorship for "Air Traffic Management".
A corresponding contract between the university and the DFS has now been signed in Worms.
The contract was initially concluded for three years and will start in 2021.
With the professorship, it is possible to enable the start of studies not only in the summer semester, but also in the winter semester.
This means that twice as many students can be trained as before.
At the same time, the capacities at the university as well as at the DFS Air Traffic Control Academy are used equally.
The DFS will advise the university on the establishment and appointment of the professorship.
Represented at the university since 2019
Since the summer semester 2019, the first students have been in the Air Traffic Management program as part of their training as air traffic controllers at Worms University of Applied Sciences.
Nine students already started this year.
So far, the experience of the DFS has been very positive and the performance of the students is excellent.
The combination of studies and pilot training significantly contributes to further increasing the attractiveness of the pilot profession.
"In these times, promotion is not easy for us economically.
However, we firmly expect air traffic to recover and grow again in the long term.
In order to continue to fulfil our legal mandate in the future, we need highly qualified personnel," says Professor Klaus-Dieter Scheurle, CEO of DFS at the signing of the contract.
"For the DFS, the foundation professorship is a future-proof investment that will provide air traffic controllers with a broad, comprehensive knowledge base in the long term.
We therefore continue the good cooperation with the university and at the same time reinforce our attractiveness as an employer".
Professor Dr. Jens Hermsdorf, President of Worms University of Applied Sciences, also underlines this: "The professorship of the foundation forms an important bridge between science and business.
With it, we would like to build on the already existing cooperation with DFS Deutsche Flugsicherung as a practical partner for the dual Bachelor's degree programme in Air Traffic Management."
For the University of Worms, the trust of Deutsche Flugsicherung is both motivation and commitment to further expand its teaching and research expertise in the future areas of aviation.
In the field of air traffic controllers of tomorrow, the university can set very special highlights and innovative priorities for its students with the first professorship for a dual course of study.
Dr. Denis Alt, State Secretary at the Ministry of Science, Continuing Education and Culture, stresses: "With its focus on aviation, the Worms University of Applied Sciences has a unique selling point in Rhineland-Palatinate.
Today's signing of the cooperation agreement strengthens the profile of the university".
